    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sample Data (Replace with your actual dataset)\n",
    "# Assuming df is your DataFrame with 'sleep_hours' and 'mental_health' columns\n",
    "data = {\n",
    "    'sleep_hours': [5, 7, 8, 6, 9, 5, 6, 8, 7, 4, 5, 8, 9, 10, 6],\n",
    "    'mental_health': ['Poor', 'Good', 'Excellent', 'Fair', 'Excellent', 'Poor', 'Fair', 'Good', 'Good', 'Poor', 'Poor', 'Excellent', 'Excellent', 'Good', 'Fair']\n",
    "}\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame(data)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Categorize sleep hours\n",
    "bins = [0, 6, 8, 12]\n",
    "labels = ['<6 hours', '6-8 hours', '>8 hours']\n",
    "df['sleep_category'] = pd.cut(df['sleep_hours'], bins=bins, labels=labels)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert mental health to a numerical scale for boxplot\n",
    "health_map = {'Poor': 1, 'Fair': 2, 'Good': 3, 'Excellent': 4}\n",
    "df['mental_health_score'] = df['mental_health'].map(health_map)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create the boxplot\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))\n",
    "sns.boxplot(x='sleep_category', y='mental_health_score', data=df)\n",
    "plt.title('Sleep Duration vs Mental Health')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Sleep Duration')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Mental Health Score')\n",
    "plt.xticks(ticks=[0, 1, 2], labels=['<6 hours', '6-8 hours', '>8 hours'])\n",
    "plt.grid(True)\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]

    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a synthetic dataset\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)  # For reproducibility\n",
    "data_size = 100  # Number of participants\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate random data for caffeine consumption (in cups) and anxiety levels\n",
    "data = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'Caffeine_Consumption': np.random.randint(0, 8, size=data_size),  # Cups of coffee per day\n",
    "    'Anxiety_Level': np.random.randint(1, 10, size=data_size)  # Anxiety level on a scale of 1 to 10\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Categorize the caffeine consumption into groups\n",
    "data['Caffeine_Group'] = pd.cut(data['Caffeine_Consumption'], bins=[0, 1, 3, 5, 8], \n",
    "                                labels=['0-1 cups', '2-3 cups', '4-5 cups', '6+ cups'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate the average anxiety level per caffeine group\n",
    "caffeine_anxiety = data.groupby('Caffeine_Group')['Anxiety_Level'].mean().reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the data\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "sns.barplot(x='Caffeine_Group', y='Anxiety_Level', data=caffeine_anxiety, palette='viridis')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Adding labels and title\n",
    "plt.title('Average Anxiety Level by Caffeine Consumption Group', fontsize=16)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Caffeine Consumption (cups per day)', fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Average Anxiety Level (scale 1-10)', fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a synthetic dataset\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)  # For reproducibility\n",
    "data_size = 100  # Number of participants\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate random data for social media usage (in hours) and depression levels\n",
    "data = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'Social_Media_Usage': np.random.uniform(0, 6, size=data_size),  # Hours of social media usage per day\n",
    "    'Depression_Level': np.random.randint(1, 10, size=data_size)  # Depression level on a scale of 1 to 10\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Categorize the social media usage into groups: <= 3 hours and > 3 hours\n",
    "data['Social_Media_Group'] = pd.cut(data['Social_Media_Usage'], bins=[0, 3, 6], \n",
    "                                    labels=['0-3 hours', '3+ hours'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate the average depression level per social media group\n",
    "social_media_depression = data.groupby('Social_Media_Group')['Depression_Level'].mean().reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the data\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "sns.barplot(x='Social_Media_Group', y='Depression_Level', data=social_media_depression, palette='coolwarm')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Adding labels and title\n",
    "plt.title('Average Depression Level by Social Media Usage Group', fontsize=16)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Social Media Usage (hours per day)', fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Average Depression Level (scale 1-10)', fontsize=12)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a synthetic dataset\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)  # For reproducibility\n",
    "data_size = 100  # Number of participants\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate random data for substance use and mental health outcomes\n",
    "data = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'Substance_Use_Frequency': np.random.choice(['No Use', 'Occasional Use', 'Regular Use'], size=data_size),\n",
    "    'Stress_Level': np.random.randint(1, 10, size=data_size),   # Stress level (1 = low, 10 = high)\n",
    "    'Anxiety_Level': np.random.randint(1, 10, size=data_size),  # Anxiety level (1 = low, 10 = high)\n",
    "    'Depression_Level': np.random.randint(1, 10, size=data_size)  # Depression level (1 = low, 10 = high)\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate the average mental health scores per substance use group\n",
    "substance_mental_health = data.groupby('Substance_Use_Frequency').mean().reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set up a figure with three subplots for Stress, Anxiety, and Depression levels\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot Stress Level\n",
    "sns.barplot(x='Substance_Use_Frequency', y='Stress_Level', data=substance_mental_health, ax=axes[0], palette='Reds')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Average Stress Level')\n",
    "axes[0].set_xlabel('Substance Use Frequency')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('Stress Level (1-10)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot Anxiety Level\n",
    "sns.barplot(x='Substance_Use_Frequency', y='Anxiety_Level', data=substance_mental_health, ax=axes[1], palette='Blues')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Average Anxiety Level')\n",
    "axes[1].set_xlabel('Substance Use Frequency')\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Anxiety Level (1-10)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot Depression Level\n",
    "sns.barplot(x='Substance_Use_Frequency', y='Depression_Level', data=substance_mental_health, ax=axes[2], palette='Purples')\n",
    "axes[2].set_title('Average Depression Level')\n",
    "axes[2].set_xlabel('Substance Use Frequency')\n",
    "axes[2].set_ylabel('Depression Level (1-10)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Adjust the layout for better spacing\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]

    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a synthetic dataset\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)  # For reproducibility\n",
    "data_size = 100  # Number of participants\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate random data for chronic illness status and mental health outcomes\n",
    "data = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'Chronic_Illness': np.random.choice(['Yes', 'No'], size=data_size),  # Chronic illness (Yes/No)\n",
    "    'Stress_Level': np.random.randint(1, 10, size=data_size),  # Stress level (1 = low, 10 = high)\n",
    "    'Mental_Health_Score': np.random.randint(1, 10, size=data_size)  # Mental health score (1 = poor, 10 = excellent)\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate the average stress level and mental health score per chronic illness group\n",
    "chronic_mental_health = data.groupby('Chronic_Illness').mean().reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set up a figure with two subplots for Stress Level and Mental Health Score\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot Stress Level\n",
    "sns.barplot(x='Chronic_Illness', y='Stress_Level', data=chronic_mental_health, ax=axes[0], palette='Reds')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Average Stress Level by Chronic Illness Status')\n",
    "axes[0].set_xlabel('Chronic Illness Status')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('Stress Level (1-10)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot Mental Health Score\n",
    "sns.barplot(x='Chronic_Illness', y='Mental_Health_Score', data=chronic_mental_health, ax=axes[1], palette='Blues')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Average Mental Health Score by Chronic Illness Status')\n",
    "axes[1].set_xlabel('Chronic Illness Status')\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Mental Health Score (1-10)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Adjust layout\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
